Testing net/transmission beyond 4.1.0.beta.2:

1) # pkg_add xz git

2) $ git clone -b obsd --recurse-submodules git@github.com:jggimi/transmission.git

      * This fork is synced with the upstream project. The obsd branch
        adds an ./archive.sh script to simplify distfile creation.

      * The port's ${PKGNAME} includes a patch level in yyyymmdd format.

      * The -daemon, -qt, and -gtk applications report a version string
        that includes the HEAD commit hash from the main branch via
        ${GIT_REVISION} in post-patch.

3) $ cd transmission; sh archive.sh 

     * This script prepares a tarball of the forked project, with submodules,
       in /usr/ports/distfiles. The script is dependent on xz and git.

4) # pkg_delete transmission

5) $ make clean=all

6) $ make makesum

7) if there are patches: `$ make patch && make update-patches`

8) $ make update-plist

9) $ make port-lib-depends-check

10) $ make install-all
